posts.cooked:
Where is the code that is trying to use the test command? I suspect it is executing before RobotContainer is constructed.

If it is in the constructor for the drive subsystem, and that’s being initialized in a field declaration in RobotContainer , then try moving the initialization part to the end of the RobotContainer constructor.

E.g.

posts.cooked:
You mispelled print, also I’m under the assumption you are pulling from a Java file based on your code. In order for it to work you need to import and initialize it.

Please referencet the pathplanner docs aswell: PathPlannerLib | PathPlanner Docs
public RobotContainer() { DriverStation.silenceJoystickConnectionWarning(true); NamedCommands.registerCommand("test", new Commands.print("Hello WORD")); }
even if you write it right it is still wrong

posts.name: Katie
posts.cooked: Where are you pulling Command.print from? And is it imported into the RobotContainer java file properly?

posts.name: Katie
posts.cooked: You need to have a constructer of Command print before you can call it in the NamedCommands.registerCommand. Please reference the wpilib docs Commands (WPILib API 2025.2.1)
